d) Purpose of assigning hostname to switch-
Identifies the device in network
Helps in management & troubleshooting
Avoids confusion in multiple devices

f) Ethical hacking-
Legal hacking done to find vulnerabilities
Used for improving security
Done with permission

g) show running-config command-
Displays current active configuration of the device (RAM)
Includes interfaces, IPs, passwords, protocols




Question-2 (B) – Option 1: Ring Topology (C Program)

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int n, i;
    printf("Enter number of nodes: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    printf("\nRing Topology Connections:\n");
    for(i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if(i == n)
            printf("Node %d -> Node 1\n", i);
        else
            printf("Node %d -> Node %d\n", i, i+1);
    }
    return 0;
}























